n about something that was not true.\n\n- Daniel\n|\nIt can't be that life is so senseless and horrible. But if it really has been so horrible and senseless, why must I die and die in agony? There is something wrong!\n\n- Leo Tolstoy, The Death of Ivan Ilych\n|\nA Gaint can easily fall to the level of an Ant but, an Anit can't rise to the level of a Gaint\n\n- Samuel\n|\nWhat comes, is called.\n\n- Ki Longfellow, Flow Down Like Silver: Hypatia of Alexandria\n|\nI do not fear death. I had been dead for billions and billions of years before I was born, and had not suffered the slightest inconvenience from it.\n\n- Mark\n|\nI need words and print... I need print like an addict. I could live without it, perhaps. But I hope I never have to try.\n\n- Margaret\n|\nThere's isn't any slight of hand in Spirituality, everything you desire is right there for you to see.\n\n- Stanley\n|\nif what is true brings us sorrow, / if what sorrow brings is truth\n\n- Robert Peake, New Poets, Short Books, Volume V\n|\nI can't decide whether I'm a good girl wrapped up in a bad girl, or if I'm a bad girl wrapped up in a good girl. And that's how I know I'm a woman!\n\n- C.\n|\nI am creative, blissful, and blessed!\n\n- Amy Leigh Mercree, Joyful Living: 101 Ways to Transform Your Spirit and Revitalize Your Life\n|\nHope is a flicker, a candle flame kept burning by the simple act of breathing.\n\n- Joan\n|\nSaki says that youth is like hors d'oeuvres: you are so busy thinking of the next courses you don't notice it. When you've had them, you wish you'd had more hors d'oeuvres.\n\n- Philip Larkin, Philip Larkin: Letters to Monica\n|\nOne ChoiceOne Choice, decided your friends.One Choice, defines your beliefs.One Choice, determines your loyalties - Forever.ONCE CHOICE CAN TRANSFORM YOU\n\n- Veronica Roth, Divergent\n|\nReligious sentiments are many a times much above reality. All are aware of reality but blinded by faith and faith has always led to many a myths become reality'.\n\n- Amit\n|\nIf